<br>
     You see, Linux is clearly not intended for ordinary users. Because these people are use to some programs and interface (@microsoft market@). That said, you can still do with Linux anything you can do with another OS... granted, its a bit harder to find the software and get used to it, but you'll save TONS of money. Outside of the &quot;World&quot; (i.e. USA), Linux is widely used by business.<br>
<br>
     En résumé, Linux profides an incredibly efficient and reliable platform for various activities. Its especially interresting for network purposes, being so stable it doesnt jamm every 2 second. <br>
