<br>
Linux WAS a pain in the fucking arse! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It was  more efficient for a lot of things like speedier copying of files, quicker loading and less crashing. <br>
<br>
But you have to pay for this.. in functionality, you can't get half of the windows software apps on Linux. Even on the things you can get, you need ports and software to get it to run, the fact of the matter is that joe average isn't going to want to do that. Which is why it will not take off.. Until people start making versions of decent software for linux.<br>
<br>
I realise linux has come a long way from the days of Linux 3! I have used 8.2 and it was a LOT easier..  I'm talking about when you had to type in commands to get your sound card working .. (emk?) shit like that.<br>
<br>
I don't think that it will take off like Windows, i've tried to manage with JUST linux, but I can't. I tried to revolt against windows, but there are just so many applications on windows that I need. Its not practical..<br>
<br>
I've got a half decent knowledge of unix by the way so before anyone says &quot;its because you don't know enough about unix&quot;.. <br>
